content.text:
You're right. External package risks: API mismatch, breaking updates, security. Better to adopt the **tokenizer approach** directly in lint-guard.ts — self-contained, no deps, exactly tailored.

## The Tokenizer Approach

Instead of regex pattern matching, parse the bash command into tokens:

```
Input:  echo "hello" | sed -i 's/a/b/g' file.txt
Tokens: ["echo", "hello"] | ["sed", "-i", "s/a/b/g", "file.txt"]
                               ↑ blocked: file-write command
```

This handles piping, chaining, quoting — robust against the regex bypasses we found.

```
Input:  cat file.ts
Tokens: ["cat", "file.ts"]
         ↑ blocked: file-read command, redirect to read tool

Input:  echo "hi" | cat
Tokens: ["echo", "hi"] | ["cat"]
         ↑ NOT blocked: cat in a pipe, not reading a file
```

## Implementation in lint-guard.ts

Replace the current `MODIFY_TOOLS` regex with a tokenizer + command tables:

```typescript
// ── Blocked bash commands with redirects ──
const BLOCKED_COMMANDS: Record<string, { category: string; redirect: string }> = {
    // File read — redirect to `read` tool
    cat:    { category: "file-read", redirect: "read" },
    head:   { category: "file-read", redirect: "read" },
    tail:   { category: "file-read", redirect: "read" },
    less:   { category: "file-read", redirect: "read" },
    more:   { category: "file-read", redirect: "read" },
    nl:     { category: "file-read", redirect: "read" },

    // File write — redirect to `edit`/`write` tool
    sed:    { category: "file-write", redirect: "edit or write" },
    awk:    { category: "file-write", redirect: "edit or write" },
    tee:    { category: "file-write", redirect: "edit or write" },
    dd:     { category: "file-write", redirect: "edit or write" },
    install:{ category: "file-write", redirect: "edit or write" },
    mv:     { category: "file-write", redirect: "edit or write" },
    cp:     { category: "file-write", redirect: "edit or write" },
};

// Check if a command uses redirect operators (> or >>)
function hasFileRedirect(cmd: string): boolean {
    return />\s*[^\s]/.test(cmd) || />>\s*[^\s]/.test(cmd);
}

function isBashModification(command: string): { blocked: boolean; reason?: string } {
    // Split by pipes to analyze each segment
    const segments = command.split(/\||;/);

    // Check for redirect operators anywhere
    if (hasFileRedirect(command)) {
        return { blocked: true, reason: "Use edit or write tool to write files, not bash redirects." };
    }

    // Check each pipe segment
    for (const segment of segments) {
        const trimmed = segment.trim();
        const firstWord = trimmed.split(/\s+/)[0]?.toLowerCase();
        if (!firstWord) continue;

        // Skip if it's a flag or option (starts with -)
        if (firstWord.startsWith("-")) continue;

        const blocked = BLOCKED_COMMANDS[firstWord];
        if (blocked) {
            return {
                blocked: true,
